# Pixel Value Comments

When setting a variable value in pixels, add a comment on the same line describing what the measurement represents.

## Format

```javascript
const variableName = 40; // description in pixels
```

## Examples

**Good:**

```javascript
const watermarkHeight = 40; // Space for watermark and margin in pixels
const padding = 20; // Text padding in pixels
const buttonSize = 50; // Button width and height in pixels
const marginTop = 65; // Top margin in pixels
```

**Avoid:**

```javascript
const watermarkHeight = 40;
const padding = 20;
const buttonSize = 50;
```

## Rules

- Comment should describe what the pixel measurement represents
- Use "in pixels" at the end of the comment for clarity
- Keep comments concise but descriptive
- Apply to any numeric value that represents pixel dimensions, spacing, or positioning
